From: PS4 Linux Baikal Port <noreply@ps4-linux>
Subject: [PATCH] net: ps4_mts v83 - AN-restart-on-link-down in phy_ctrl kthread

v82 confirmed the kthread-heartbeat hypothesis - SMI MDC stays alive
across >5 min uptime thanks to BMSR-every-3s.  But link remained DOWN
despite the PHY reporting AN-complete (BMSR bit 5 set) and the link
partner advertising (reg 5 = 0xc5e1).  linkreg bit 0 stayed 0.

This patch mirrors Orbis FUN_c85f0480 event 0x1 handler verbatim:
when linkreg bit 0 = 0 (link down), the phy_ctrl thread does:

  reg 9 (1000-BT control)  |= 0x0200  (advertise 1000-BT full)
  reg 4 (ANAR)             |= 0x0180  (advertise 100BX full+half)
  reg 0 (BMCR)             |= 0x1200  (AN enable + AN restart)

To avoid restarting AN on every 3s iteration (which would prevent AN
from completing), the kthread tracks UP/DOWN transitions and restarts
AN only on:
  - The very first iteration (initial bring-up from boot)
  - Every UP->DOWN transition
  - Every 5 iterations (~15s) while link still down, as a retry

Once link comes UP the retry counter resets and only heartbeat reads
happen.

If link stays DOWN even with periodic AN restarts: the MT7531 needs
MMD vendor writes that we haven't implemented (mainline mt7530-mdio.c
does extensive vendor init).  v84 would be the place to add those if
needed.

Pass criterion: dmesg shows
  ps4_mts ...: phy_ctrl: AN restart (iter=0, BMCR<-0x1240 or similar)
followed within a few seconds by
  ps4_mts ...: phy_ctrl: link UP (linkreg=0x????)

And `ip link show` would eventually show a netdev (... if we had one;
netdev allocation is phase 3).  For now, link-up evidence is in
linkreg bit 0 = 1 visible via the userspace BAR0 mmap.
---
--- a/drivers/net/ethernet/sony/ps4_mts.c
+++ b/drivers/net/ethernet/sony/ps4_mts.c
@@ -109,6 +109,9 @@
 	struct task_struct *phy_ctrl_thread;
 	u8 phy_addr;
 	bool link_logged_once;
+	bool last_phy_link_up;	/* tracked by phy_ctrl kthread */
+	bool initial_an_done;	/* first AN restart fired? */
+	unsigned int link_down_iterations;
 };
 
 /*
@@ -318,33 +321,103 @@
 }
 
 /*
- * SMI heartbeat thread.  Orbis's gbe:phy_ctrl (FUN_c85f0480) reads BMSR every
- * 3 seconds in its main loop, which exercises the full SMI handshake (ARM,
- * OP_RD, poll DONE, fetch data) and keeps the MDC clock domain from gating
- * off.  Per the 2026-05-12 4-agent dig (glm-5.1 + kimi-k2.6), the SMI clock
- * is transaction-gated, not enable-bit-gated - restoring registers can't
- * recover MDC, only ongoing bus traffic can.
+ * AN restart sequence.  Mirrors Orbis FUN_c85f0480 event 0x1 handler exactly:
+ * read 1000-BT control (reg 9) and ANAR (reg 4), OR-set the advertise bits if
+ * not present, then write BMCR (reg 0) with bit 12 (AN enable) + bit 9 (AN
+ * restart) set.  This is the "kick AN into action" sequence the Orbis driver
+ * uses on every link-down event.
  *
- * Phase-1 of this thread is intentionally minimal: just BMSR every 3s, no AN
- * restart, no link-change handling.  We want to first confirm the heartbeat
- * hypothesis (does MDC survive >5min?) before adding state.  The full Orbis
- * state machine (BMSR poll + AN restart on timeout + reg 9 advertise +
- * BMCR 0x1200 restart) will follow if v82 boots clean.
+ * Returns the post-restart BMCR for logging.
+ */
+static u16 mts_phy_an_restart(struct mts *mts)
+{
+	u16 ctrl_1000bt, anar, bmcr;
+
+	mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x09, &ctrl_1000bt);
+	mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x04, &anar);
+
+	if (!(ctrl_1000bt & 0x0200))
+		mts_smi_c22_write(mts, 0x09, ctrl_1000bt | 0x0200);
+	if ((anar & 0x0180) != 0x0180)
+		mts_smi_c22_write(mts, 0x04, anar | 0x0180);
+
+	mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x00, &bmcr);
+	mts_smi_c22_write(mts, 0x00, bmcr | 0x1200);
+	return bmcr | 0x1200;
+}
+
+/*
+ * SMI heartbeat + link bring-up thread.
+ *
+ * Two responsibilities:
+ *   1) MDC heartbeat: every 3s the loop touches the SMI bus, which keeps the
+ *      transaction-gated MDC clock domain alive.  v82 confirmed this is the
+ *      sole way to prevent MDC death.
+ *   2) Link bring-up: mirrors Orbis FUN_c85f0480 event 0x1 — on every UP->DOWN
+ *      transition AND on the first iteration (initial bring-up from boot),
+ *      run mts_phy_an_restart().  Retry every 5 iterations (~15s) while link
+ *      stays down to handle AN that didn't latch the first time.  Stops
+ *      retrying as soon as link comes up.
+ *
+ * Note: in Orbis the AN-restart is event-driven via mts_intr signaling
+ * softc->event_phy_ctrl with bit 0x1.  We don't have an ISR yet (phase 3
+ * work) so this thread polls linkreg directly.  Slightly more aggressive than
+ * Orbis but correct in steady state.
  */
 static int mts_phy_ctrl_fn(void *data)
 {
 	struct mts *mts = data;
+	u32 linkreg;
 	u16 bmsr;
+	bool link_up, was_up;
 	int ret;
 
 	while (!kthread_should_stop()) {
-		ret = mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x01, &bmsr);
-		if (ret == 0)
-			dev_dbg(&mts->pdev->dev,
-				"phy_ctrl: BMSR=0x%04x\n", bmsr);
-		else
-			dev_dbg(&mts->pdev->dev,
-				"phy_ctrl: SMI read timeout\n");
+		linkreg = readl(mts->bar + MTS_LINK_STATUS);
+		link_up = (linkreg & MTS_LINK_UP) != 0;
+		was_up = mts->last_phy_link_up;
+
+		if (link_up && !was_up) {
+			dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
+				 "phy_ctrl: link UP (linkreg=0x%08x)\n",
+				 linkreg);
+			mts->link_down_iterations = 0;
+		}
+		if (!link_up && was_up) {
+			dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
+				 "phy_ctrl: link DOWN (linkreg=0x%08x)\n",
+				 linkreg);
+		}
+		mts->last_phy_link_up = link_up;
+
+		if (!link_up) {
+			bool first = !mts->initial_an_done;
+			bool transition = was_up;
+			bool retry = (mts->link_down_iterations % 5) == 0
+				     && mts->link_down_iterations > 0;
+
+			if (first || transition || retry) {
+				u16 bmcr_post = mts_phy_an_restart(mts);
+				dev_info(&mts->pdev->dev,
+					 "phy_ctrl: AN restart (iter=%u, BMCR<-0x%04x)\n",
+					 mts->link_down_iterations, bmcr_post);
+				mts->initial_an_done = true;
+			} else {
+				/* Heartbeat-only read while waiting for AN. */
+				ret = mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x01, &bmsr);
+				if (ret)
+					dev_dbg(&mts->pdev->dev,
+						"phy_ctrl: SMI heartbeat read failed\n");
+			}
+			mts->link_down_iterations++;
+		} else {
+			/* Link up: just heartbeat. */
+			ret = mts_smi_c22_read(mts, 0x01, &bmsr);
+			if (ret)
+				dev_dbg(&mts->pdev->dev,
+					"phy_ctrl: SMI heartbeat read failed\n");
+		}
+
 		msleep_interruptible(MTS_PHY_CTRL_PERIOD_MS);
 	}
 	return 0;
